parameters: The door is covered in strange, fleshy plant-like growths.
Use Herbicide to clear the way?
A list of coordinates, each dated about ten months ago, taken
a few days apart. The coordinates seem to gradually change.
It's so easy to miss. A\C[14] missing star\C[0] in the full night sky. If I
stopped looking for it for a while, I could easily lose it forever.
I have an \C[3]incredible feeling\C[0] about this.
For a period of two weeks, the dates have \C[14]no coordinates,\C[0] just
A note reads: \C[3]'It moved behind a cluster of stars closer to us.
We can only observe it when in front of stars farther away.'
The coordinates return a few days later.
'It's back. It's bigger. It's moving faster. Is it \C[3]getting closer?'
Another note a week later. \C[3]'It's getting closer'.
